hu.unideb.kgsoft.scrabble

Class Tray

  • java.lang.Object
    • hu.unideb.kgsoft.scrabble.Tray

  • public class Tray
extends Object
    The Tray class represents the tray in the game, on which a player places his/her letter tiles drawn from the bag. A Tray object stores the tile codes of the letters tiles on it and the number of letter tiles currently placed on it. Basic operations are adding a tile to the tray or picking one up from it with a specific index position or in general.
    Author:
    gergo

      • getLettersAsString

        public String getLettersAsString()
        Returns all the letters from the tray concatenated as a String.
        Returns:

      • pickTile

        public int pickTile(int index)
        Returns the tile code from the given index from the tray, and replaces the tile code value on the tray with -1. If there is no tile at the given index, or the index is greater than the TRAY_SIZE, the returned value is -1.
        Parameters:
        index - the index on the tray from which the tile will be picked up
        Returns:
        the tile code from the given position from the tray or -1 if there is no tile or the index is too large

      • setTile

        public boolean setTile(int tileCode,
                       int index)
        Places a tile with the given tile code on the tray at the given index if possible. If there was no tile at the index, returns true indicating success, otherwise returns false.
        Parameters:
        tileCode - the code of the tile to be placed on the tray
        index - the index where the tile should be placed
        Returns:
        true if the tile could be placed, false otherwise

      • addTile

        public boolean addTile(int code)
        Adds the given tile code to the first available position on the tray. Returns true if the tile has been successfully added, meaning there was still place left on the tray, false otherwise.
        Parameters:
        code - the tile code that should be added to the tray
        Returns:
        true if the tile has been successfully added, false otherwise

      • removeTile

        public boolean removeTile(int code)
        Removes the first occurrence of a tile with the given tile code from the tray. The tile code on the tray at this position will be replaced by -1. Returns true if the removal was successful, false if there was no tile on the tray with the given tile code.
        Parameters:
        code - the code of the tile to be removed
        Returns:
        true if the removal is successful, false if couldn't find the tile code on the tray

      • getNumOfLetters

        public int getNumOfLetters()
        Returns the number of letters on the tray. It is advisable to check if the number of letters is less than the size of the tray, before calling the addTile method.
        Returns:
        the number of letters on the tray

      • getTileCodeAt

        public int getTileCodeAt(int index)
        Returns the tile code of the tile from the tray, from the given index. The return value is -1 if there is not tile at the given index.
        Parameters:
        index - the index on the tray
        Returns:
        a tile code or -1 if there is no tile at the given index

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Resets the tray to its initial state, with no letters. All tile codes are set to -1. Should be used for testing only.

      • setLetters

        public void setLetters(int[] letters)
        Sets the letter tile codes on the tray. Receives an array of integers with the tile codes. Should be used for testing only.
        Parameters:
        letters - the array containing the new letter tile codes
